   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessing Population Mobility Dynamics and Patterns
To Strengthen the Ebola Virus Disease Readiness Activities In Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this IOM project is to contribute to the prevention and detection of an eventual EVD outbreak, through improving access to data on population mobility mapping information. With this CERF grant, IOM will conduct district level population mobility mapping (PMM) around selected priority health districts to inform public health interventions through four reports. The project will last six months and will benefit 89,695 people.</narrative>
  </description>
